1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:03,740
When I think about it,
I completely understand.

2
00:00:04,110 --> 00:00:06,410
It's my fault
your only sister and your niece...

3
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:08,810
are gone.

4
00:00:10,050 --> 00:00:12,680
I can only imagine how much
you must have wanted to kill me.

5
00:00:14,450 --> 00:00:16,490
There's nothing I can say for myself.

6
00:00:16,820 --> 00:00:17,820
Listen.

7
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:22,660
I came all this way because I have
something important to tell you.

8
00:00:23,290 --> 00:00:24,300
What is it?

9
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,700
Our Eun Hye...

10
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:27,900
isn't dead.

11
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:29,830
What...

12
00:00:30,940 --> 00:00:32,300
What did you just say?

13
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:33,810
Our Eun Hye,

14
00:00:34,370 --> 00:00:37,010
your daughter, who you've believed
was dead all this time,

15
00:00:38,010 --> 00:00:40,010
is alive.

16
00:00:40,810 --> 00:00:41,810
What?

17
00:00:42,950 --> 00:00:44,050
My Eun Hye...

18
00:00:44,950 --> 00:00:46,120
is alive?

19
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:53,430
You're not just saying this to comfort me,
are you? Right?

20
00:00:54,130 --> 00:00:55,190
My daughter...

21
00:00:55,790 --> 00:01:00,100
didn't die in that cold water back then,

22
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:03,540
and she's alive right now? Is that right?

23
00:01:04,170 --> 00:01:07,740
Seong Hye, this isn't a dream, is it?

24
00:01:07,810 --> 00:01:09,310
It's not a dream.

25
00:01:09,810 --> 00:01:13,880
I heard it with my own ears.
Eun Hye is alive.

26
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:17,680
Oh, thank goodness.

27
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:22,690
Oh, thank you.

28
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:26,590
Oh, Eun Hye!

29
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,910
I'm not going to lose it this time.

30
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,870
I'll make sure Grandfather
gets his present.

31
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:52,150
So then,

32
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:55,520
where is my Eun Hye?

33
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:58,020
Can I see her right away?

34
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:00,390
What am I doing sitting here?

35
00:02:00,390 --> 00:02:02,560
Let's go find our Eun Hye.

36
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:05,060
Dae Chang, calm down. Sit down.

37
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,770
I don't know where she is yet.

38
00:02:07,770 --> 00:02:09,330
We have to start looking for her now.

39
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:12,840
I came here so we could find her together.

40
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:15,440
I dropped everything in America
and came straight here.

41
00:02:20,580 --> 00:02:21,610
Wait, then...

42
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:27,450
how did you find out
that Eun Hye is alive?

43
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,760
Of all places, on a street in Koreatown,

44
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:33,530
I ran into that woman.

45
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:36,330
The housekeeper who took Eun Hye.

46
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:39,060
- And?
- She tried to run, but I grabbed her.

47
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,670
I went off on her,
asking how she dared to show her face.

48
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:52,440
She said Eun Hye
didn't actually die that day.

49
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:54,550
Then what happened?

50
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:57,550
At the time,
that awful housekeeper of ours...

51
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,020
sold our Eun Hye to a broker.

52
00:03:00,550 --> 00:03:01,850
That broker scum was...

53
00:03:01,850 --> 00:03:04,860
boarding a ship at Incheon Port
when the police caught him.

54
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:09,860
He tried to run, fell in the water,
and Eun Hye drowned.

55
00:03:09,930 --> 00:03:13,130
But she said that child wasn't Eun Hye.

56
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:21,740
Gosh, that's bitter.

57
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:24,710
Why does this soju...

58
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,380
have to be so bitter, just like my life?

59
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,350
Why...

60
00:03:30,950 --> 00:03:32,020
What in the world...

61
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:35,350
are those two even doing in the study?

62
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:38,860
Darn it.

63
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:40,660
I'm so furious.

64
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:43,390
I'm so angry!

65
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,970
I can't just sit back.

66
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:51,440
I'm not letting her take my place
from right under my nose.

67
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:00,480
Then, back then,

68
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:04,320
who was the child that drowned?

69
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:07,920
She said it was another child
the broker had with him.

70
00:04:09,090 --> 00:04:13,460
The broker was being chased with two kids,
and in his panic,

71
00:04:13,730 --> 00:04:16,930
he just abandoned our Eun Hye somewhere
and got on the boat.

72
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,730
He probably couldn't run with two kids.

73
00:04:20,770 --> 00:04:24,540
The housekeeper met that scumbag broker
ten years later,

74
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:28,610
and that's when she heard
that Eun Hye hadn't died.

75
00:04:28,710 --> 00:04:32,580
Why didn't she say something then?

76
00:04:32,910 --> 00:04:36,880
She was too scared. If you caught her,
you'd tear her apart.

77
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:41,120
So she just stayed on the run
and kept her mouth shut all this time.

78
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:42,250
Goodness...

79
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:47,060
It's all my fault.

80
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:51,830
When we heard something awful
had happened to Eun Hye,

81
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:54,330
Seong Sil became bedridden with grief.

82
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,740
- Oh, goodness.
- But...

83
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,170
they're saying Eun Hye is alive.

84
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,740
That's a huge relief, isn't it?

85
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:06,610
Of course.

86
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:08,610
Now that we know she's alive,

87
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:11,280
we have to find her no matter what.

88
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,950
We have to.

89
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:15,320
We have to find her, whatever it takes.

90
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:17,820
Oh, my poor girl.

91
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:22,460
She's spent her whole life
wandering around,

92
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:25,630
not even knowing who her parents are.

93
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:30,270
Oh, my poor, pitiful girl.

94
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:35,910
I abandoned my daughter to the world
all these years.

95
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:38,940
How could a worthless father like me...

96
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:42,410
even go on living?

97
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,580
Goodness.

98
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:47,690
After my sister lost Eun Hye,

99
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:51,260
she died so young from a broken heart.

100
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:56,690
I blamed you for everything that happened.
And I resented you so much.

101
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:01,530
I'm so sorry.

102
00:06:02,770 --> 00:06:03,800
No, don't be.

103
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:07,840
If I hadn't gone bankrupt back then...

104
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:11,910
No, it's all my fault.

105
00:06:12,410 --> 00:06:14,680
It all happened because of me.

106
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:18,820
I'm so sorry, Seong Hye. Okay?

107
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:28,960
Well, isn't this a touching scene?

108
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:34,830
My, what a tearful reunion.
Did you miss each other that much?

109
00:06:35,370 --> 00:06:38,000
I had no idea you two were so close.

110
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:44,040
I've been here all this time,
dedicating my entire life to this family.

111
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,580
Finally, at long last,

112
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:49,380
I've been tossed aside like an old shoe.

113
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,780
I'm getting tipsy.

114
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:55,290
What do you think you're doing?

115
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:58,560
- Get out!
- I'm not leaving.

116
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,190
Why should I be the one to leave?

117
00:07:00,530 --> 00:07:03,630
- I'm not leaving!
- What is wrong with you!

118
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,300
- I won't leave.
- Get out right now!

119
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:09,300
I'm not leaving.
You'll have to kill me! Go on, kill me!

120
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:12,500
- I'm not leaving! I won't!
- Hey, what's all this commotion?

121
00:07:12,570 --> 00:07:14,340
- Let's go.
- Let go of me!

122
00:07:14,340 --> 00:07:16,610
- What are you doing?
- I won't leave.

123
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:18,910
- I'm not leaving! Kill me instead!
- Just unbelievable.

124
00:07:18,910 --> 00:07:22,410
Just kill me! Alright?
You hear me? I'm not leaving!

125
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,820
Goodness!

126
00:07:50,780 --> 00:07:52,080
Excuse me.

127
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:58,450
Goodness, thank you.

128
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,820
Not at all.

129
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:06,320
If it weren't for you, Manager Lee,
I could have been badly injured.

130
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:10,390
Are you hurt anywhere?

131
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:14,400
I'm fine, thanks to you.

132
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,030
But Manager Lee, your suit...

133
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:19,670
Oh no. I've spilled it all over you.

134
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,670
Oh, it's fine.

135
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:23,370
What am I going to do?

136
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,750
Please, take it off.

137
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,380
- Excuse me?
- Your suit jacket.

138
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:35,150
Take it off and give it to me.
I'll get it dry-cleaned.

139
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:37,390
And the floor...

140
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:41,830
- Oh my, what a mess.
- The cleaning staff can take care of it.

141
00:08:42,930 --> 00:08:44,560
Please, just give it to me.

142
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:47,230
I feel too guilty to just walk away.

143
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,600
But...

144
00:08:49,170 --> 00:08:50,300
it's really no trouble.

145
00:08:51,370 --> 00:08:54,310
You saved me from injuring my back.

146
00:08:54,370 --> 00:08:55,370
No, actually,

147
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:57,910
I would've hurt more than just my back.

148
00:08:58,110 --> 00:08:59,610
At my age, if I'd hit my head,

149
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:02,580
I could have been paralyzed!

150
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:08,320
On top of that, I've ruined your suit.
How could I possibly just leave?

151
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,290
It just wouldn't be right.

152
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:13,620
Please.

153
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:15,590
Gosh.

154
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:18,560
All right then.

155
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:23,600
Here, please take care of it.

156
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,970
I'll get it cleaned
and bring it right back to you.

157
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:27,610
Okay. Thank you.

158
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:38,650
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

159
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:40,250
I'm here, Jun Ho.

160
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:44,590
Here we go again.

161
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,760
Can't you see I'm working?

162
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:51,360
Do you have any idea
how much I missed you?

163
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:56,330
You have no self-respect, do you, Seo Rin?

164
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:01,170
I made it perfectly clear how I feel,
but you just keep coming back.

165
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:04,780
You're one to talk, aren't you?

166
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:08,880
The way you can't give up on Oh Jang Mi,
who's about to marry Kang Baek Ho.

167
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:12,180
Talk about the pot
calling the kettle black.

168
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:15,420
You might want to see it that way,

169
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:17,690
but your situation and mine
are completely different.

170
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:20,690
If you had shown up
just 30 minutes later that day,

171
00:10:21,290 --> 00:10:22,990
I would've married Jang Mi.

172
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,230
I was the one...

173
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:28,730
Jang Mi wanted to spend her life with.

174
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:33,140
Oh Jang Mi was just pretending to be me,
and you fell for her thinking she was me.

175
00:10:33,370 --> 00:10:34,370
No.

176
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:36,270
I made myself clear.

177
00:10:37,010 --> 00:10:38,980
It wasn't Ma Seo Rin I fell in love with,

178
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:41,310
it was Oh Jang Mi.

179
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:43,610
Kang Jun Ho.

180
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:45,520
I guess you're not
as ambitious as I thought.

181
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:48,420
Don't you want Dream?
Who cares about love?

182
00:10:48,490 --> 00:10:49,820
Not when you can have Dream!

183
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:53,120
Don't delude yourself, Ma Seo Rin.

184
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,630
Do you think you're the only way
I can get Dream?

185
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:58,800
I can still get Dream
even if I choose Oh Jang Mi.

186
00:10:59,030 --> 00:11:00,030
So then,

187
00:11:01,570 --> 00:11:03,370
is there no place for me
in your ambitions?

188
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:08,710
Why her and not me?

189
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,640
Jang Mi has a warmth to her.

190
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,410
A warmth you could never have,

191
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,080
not in a million years.

192
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,250
Get this straight, Ma Seo Rin.

193
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,750
I will have Oh Jang Mi,

194
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:22,790
and I'm going to take Dream.

195
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,560
No! I won't let you!

196
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,540
- Seo Rin.
- Oh Jang Mi,

197
00:11:39,170 --> 00:11:40,300
we need to talk.

198
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:51,680
- You tramp.
- Ma Seo Rin.

199
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:53,050
What do you think you're doing?

200
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,020
"What am I doing?" That's my line.

201
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,990
What did you do to wrap Jun Ho
around your finger,

202
00:11:59,060 --> 00:12:01,790
making him so crazy about you?

203
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:03,260
Seo Rin,

204
00:12:03,730 --> 00:12:07,260
- it's a misunderstanding.
- I regret ever meeting you.

205
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:11,100
I should've pretended not to know
we were twins when I found out.

206
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,940
You're the biggest regret of my life.

207
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:17,740
I regret listening to that family talk!

208
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:18,940
I'm sorry.

209
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:20,740
I'm so sorry, Seo Rin.

210
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:24,950
But just know that
you have nothing to lose.

211
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:28,290
I would never take anything that's yours.
I swear.

212
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,160
I...

213
00:12:32,690 --> 00:12:34,090
I'm marrying Baek Ho tomorrow.

214
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:37,330
So you don't have to worry about a thing,
okay?

215
00:12:38,030 --> 00:12:39,030
Seo Rin.

216
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:48,470
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

217
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,840
Jun Ho.

218
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:53,540
Good, you're here.

219
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:02,190
I decided to cook something special today.

220
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,760
You know your mom's not the best cook,
right?

221
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:11,330
But I still tried my best for my son,
so come and have a bite, okay?

222
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,100
Here.

223
00:13:21,140 --> 00:13:23,010
You don't have to go
through all this trouble.

224
00:13:24,310 --> 00:13:25,310
A person's heart...

225
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:27,010
and love...

226
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,980
You can't force those things.

227
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:36,520
Jun Ho... I'm sorry.

228
00:13:36,990 --> 00:13:40,260
- Please don't be upset.
- Just do whatever you want.

229
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:43,160
I'm just an outsider here anyway.

230
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:57,270
I just can't figure you out, Baek Ho.

231
00:13:57,540 --> 00:13:59,640
- What?
- Don't you have any ambition?

232
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:02,550
If you choose Oh Jang Mi,
you'll lose Dream.

233
00:14:02,810 --> 00:14:05,720
- What are you talking about?
- A man should have some ambition.

234
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,950
Seo Rin is going to inherit Dream,
and there's me, the daughter of the house.

235
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:13,020
So why marry Oh Jang Mi?
There's nothing in it for you.

236
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,830
So, Hong Ju, are you saying
you only like me for my background?

237
00:14:16,330 --> 00:14:17,460
I don't really have much to offer.

238
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:20,700
That's not it.
I like you, Baek Ho, for who you...

239
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:24,840
- I like you as you are. That's why...
- Me too.

240
00:14:25,370 --> 00:14:27,840
I've liked Jang Mi ever since
she worked at the side dish store.

241
00:14:28,770 --> 00:14:30,470
Whether she becomes the head of Dream...

242
00:14:30,470 --> 00:14:32,280
or goes back to working
at the side dish store,

243
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,850
I love her for who she is.

244
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,120
Also, I'm about to be off the market,

245
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:40,880
so you should move on quickly
and find someone else.

246
00:14:41,650 --> 00:14:42,650
Bye.

247
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:50,790
"Off the market," my foot.
You're not even married yet.

248
00:14:53,730 --> 00:14:55,100
Hello, Geum Soon? What is it?

249
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,640
What? My mom's drunk and making a scene?

250
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:13,320
After you were arrested
and my sister went to the States to work,

251
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,920
she apparently put a necklace
on her daughter, Eun Hye.

252
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,860
It's the one you gave my sister as a gift.

253
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:21,060
You know, that heart necklace?

254
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:25,460
(Sil)

255
00:15:26,330 --> 00:15:27,800
My Eun Hye...

256
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:30,530
must have one engraved...

257
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:35,040
with "Chang,"
the last character of my name.

258
00:15:41,410 --> 00:15:44,350
- Uncle, what's that box?
- This?

259
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:47,350
I think they're Grandfather's things.
I'm just trying to sort through them.

260
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:50,090
Oh? This belongs to Bok Gil.

261
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:53,720
Good for you, Mom.
You even remember this old box.

262
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:55,590
Let's see.

263
00:16:02,370 --> 00:16:04,970
What? Mom, you name is written on this.

264
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:08,440
That's mine. Suk Hee. That's my name.

265
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:12,680
Why would Dad leave this necklace here?

266
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:15,850
But where's its match?
This looks like it's only half of a set.

267
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:19,320
You're right.
And this necklace looks really old.

268
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,950
Like it's decades old.

269
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:26,020
But why did Dad keep it
instead of giving it to Mom?

270
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:29,690
It's mine. It's Suk Hee's.

271
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:32,400
Suk Hee likes necklaces.

272
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,160
Okay, Mom, it's yours.

273
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:41,870
This contains the files I've put together
about what happened back then.

274
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:44,070
There's also some information
from the police.

275
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:46,880
- Yes, sir.
- I want you to search...

276
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:48,880
every single orphanage...

277
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,610
and childcare facility
near Incheon Port...

278
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,280
that existed in those days.

279
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:54,350
You have to find her.

280
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:56,620
Spare no expense.

281
00:16:56,890 --> 00:17:00,020
Do whatever it takes
to find her as soon as possible.

282
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:04,430
And this stays between you and me.

283
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:08,100
- Understood?
- Yes, I understand perfectly, Chairman.

284
00:17:15,670 --> 00:17:17,110
Eun Hye.

285
00:17:18,110 --> 00:17:21,150
Wherever you are,
I just pray you're safe and well.

286
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:22,650
Your father...

287
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:25,150
will find you soon.

288
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:34,960
Mom.

289
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,560
Mom, wake up.

290
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:38,230
Drink this honey tea
before you go back to sleep.

291
00:17:39,530 --> 00:17:41,370
Gosh, you reek of alcohol.

292
00:17:41,930 --> 00:17:44,330
How much did you have to drink?

293
00:17:48,610 --> 00:17:50,540
The whole room reeks of alcohol.

294
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:53,910
Look at you.
Do you drink yourself stupid now?

295
00:17:53,910 --> 00:17:55,150
Real classy.

296
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:00,620
I'm not going to let that witch
get away with this.

297
00:18:01,350 --> 00:18:03,120
She's already got the Chairman
wrapped around her finger.

298
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:06,460
Yeom San Wol, you're supposed to be
caring for the Chairman, not drinking.

299
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,590
What do you think you're doing?

300
00:18:08,330 --> 00:18:10,430
You think I'm drinking for fun?

301
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:13,500
Am I supposed to just watch
the Chairman...

302
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:18,070
get cozy with his old flame
from America in broad daylight?

303
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:21,510
- What? An old flame?
- Yes.

304
00:18:21,510 --> 00:18:23,210
Said she was from America.

305
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:27,680
They were holed up in the study,
having a tearful reunion.

306
00:18:28,780 --> 00:18:31,050
It just broke my heart to see it.

307
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:34,820
What? The Chairman was crying?

308
00:18:34,820 --> 00:18:36,050
That's right.

309
00:18:36,150 --> 00:18:40,720
They were holding hands,
and both of them were crying.

310
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:43,790
And it was all so painfully romantic.

311
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,500
Goodness.

312
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:51,940
Father's old flame?

313
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:54,840
I wonder who it is.

314
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:58,040
(Bomdama)

315
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:03,380
This is Suk Hee's.

316
00:19:03,650 --> 00:19:04,820
It's beautiful, Mom.

317
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:06,550
(Chang)

318
00:19:06,550 --> 00:19:09,250
Is this platinum?
It must have been expensive.

319
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:13,090
Mom, don't you dare lose that, okay?

320
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:15,530
Okay, I got it. It's Suk Hee's.

321
00:19:16,290 --> 00:19:19,400
Wait, so Jang Mi and Baek Ho
are having a private ceremony?

322
00:19:19,630 --> 00:19:22,530
First, they're having a private ceremony,
just between them.

323
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,330
And then have a bigger wedding
with everyone later.

324
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:27,770
That makes sense. It feels like yesterday
she was planning to marry Kang Jun Ho.

325
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:29,140
She can't throw another big wedding
right away.

326
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:33,510
Baek Ho is so thoughtful.
He's clearly doing all this for Jang Mi.

327
00:19:33,580 --> 00:19:36,110
Of course. He's my buddy.

328
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:38,320
He's a great guy. I learn a lot from him.

329
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:48,190
Are you picking up my dry cleaning?

330
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:50,790
You wish.

331
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,300
These aren't your clothes, Kang Nam Bong.

332
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:55,870
It's Manager Lee Kang Hyuk's suit.

333
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:57,500
What?

334
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:01,510
Why are you picking up Manager Lee's suit?

335
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,510
Good question. I wonder why.

336
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,950
I can't believe this woman.

337
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,750
What's going on?

338
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:20,260
I'm asking
why you have Manager Lee's suit.

339
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:24,530
Whose suit I carry home
is none of your business.

340
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,330
- Are you really going to be like this?
- What did I do?

341
00:20:27,330 --> 00:20:28,970
Why are you trying
to get a rise out of me?

342
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,870
Manager Lee is a thug.

343
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:36,370
He's the type who'll beat someone up
if they get on his bad side.

344
00:20:37,910 --> 00:20:39,740
That's ridiculous.

345
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:43,410
I guess you're speaking from experience.

346
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,350
Have you actually seen him hit someone?

347
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:49,220
Why are you bad-mouthing
an innocent person?

348
00:20:49,420 --> 00:20:52,190
Do I have to see it to know?
You can tell just by looking at him.

349
00:20:52,190 --> 00:20:54,160
Shut up and get out.

350
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:58,630
Even if you live in this house,
can you please just stay out of my sight?

351
00:20:58,830 --> 00:21:01,370
The very sight of you makes my skin crawl.

352
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:05,300
If you can't stand the sight of me,
just sign the divorce papers already.

353
00:21:05,370 --> 00:21:09,310
I told you.
I'm never going to give you what you want.

354
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:14,180
You must answer for your crimes
for there to be any justice.

355
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:15,580
To that end,

356
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:20,320
I'll repay you for the pain you caused me.
Just you wait.

357
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:22,990
You think you'll find peace by hating me?

358
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:25,460
In the end, you're only hurting yourself.

359
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:30,160
No. I don't even hate you anymore.

360
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:32,630
You have to care to feel hatred.

361
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,560
And I feel absolutely nothing for you.

362
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:39,400
Don't just stand there. Get out.
I need to change, so get out of my room.

363
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:41,540
Fine.

364
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:44,170
Honestly.

365
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:54,020
Seo Rin, why are you crying?

366
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:56,820
It just feels like...

367
00:21:57,820 --> 00:22:00,160
it was better when I was in a coma.

368
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:04,800
Is it because of my face?
Nobody is happy that I'm back.

369
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:10,970
I don't think I can ever be
the Ma Seo Rin I used to be again.

370
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:16,470
Seo Rin, why are you so down?
This isn't like you.

371
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:18,810
I'm right here
welcoming you with open arms.

372
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:24,350
Do you really think I can take over Dream?

373
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:26,580
Of course you will.

374
00:22:26,780 --> 00:22:30,390
And will I really be able to
win over Jun Ho?

375
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:34,420
I heard Kang Baek Ho and Oh Jang Mi
are getting married tomorrow.

376
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:36,760
So what do you think
Jun Ho is going to do?

377
00:22:37,260 --> 00:22:39,760
He'll have no choice
but to marry you. Right?

378
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:41,600
But still...

379
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:44,740
But Jun Ho doesn't love me.

380
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:48,770
Don't worry, Seo Rin.

381
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:51,070
I'll get you that plastic surgery
right away.

382
00:22:51,710 --> 00:22:55,880
Once you get your old face back,
Jun Ho will fall in love with you.

383
00:22:56,210 --> 00:22:58,980
I'll do everything I can
to help you, okay?

384
00:23:09,490 --> 00:23:10,490
Jang Mi.

385
00:23:19,470 --> 00:23:22,110
Jang Mi, you are...

386
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:25,010
the bright light of my life.

387
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:27,310
After I met you,

388
00:23:28,010 --> 00:23:30,350
that desperate feeling of wanting
to make someone happy...

389
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:33,220
is something I felt
for the very first time.

390
00:23:34,420 --> 00:23:36,750
Thank you so much.

391
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:41,020
Baek Ho, when my world came crashing down,

392
00:23:41,590 --> 00:23:44,690
you reached out your hand to me,
and I'm so grateful.

393
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:48,570
Honestly, the path ahead of me
is so difficult...

394
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,270
that I didn't want to drag you into it,

395
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,200
but now I realize something.

396
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:58,740
As long as I can walk it with you,
any path becomes a path of flowers.

397
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:02,250
I, Kang Baek Ho,

398
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:05,880
in front of my beloved bride, Oh Jang Mi,

399
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:08,690
make these vows.

400
00:24:09,820 --> 00:24:11,320
Though the world may test us,

401
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:16,090
and though we may face unbearable storms,

402
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:20,830
I will be the steady rock she can lean on.

403
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,070
I, Oh Jang Mi,

404
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:29,610
in good times and in bad,

405
00:24:30,170 --> 00:24:32,080
promise to stand by your side
and hold your hand,

406
00:24:32,980 --> 00:24:36,480
and to always be on your side,
no matter what.

407
00:24:37,010 --> 00:24:41,120
I vow this before the church and you,
Kang Baek Ho.

408
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,470
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

409
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:39,110
- Team Leader Jin, what's up?
- Jun Ho, where are you?

410
00:25:39,910 --> 00:25:42,150
Are you at the office
working on a Saturday?

411
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,410
This is no time to be working!

412
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:47,350
You have to stop Oh Jang Mi
and Kang Baek Ho from getting married!

413
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:50,020
They're getting married
at the church right now!

414
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:53,460
They're all excited to leave
on their honeymoon right after.

415
00:25:54,090 --> 00:25:55,930
Are you really going to let
Oh Jang Mi go just like that?

416
00:25:56,190 --> 00:25:58,430
- A honeymoon?
- That's what I said!

417
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:01,400
Jun Ho, please, you have to stop them.

418
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,530
I can't give up on Baek Ho.

419
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:05,900
All right. Thanks for the heads-up.

420
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:08,070
Team Leader Jin.

421
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:10,770
There's something I need you to do.

422
00:26:12,510 --> 00:26:17,550
<i>The look in your eyes when we first met</i>

423
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:25,360
<i>Was it all in my head?</i>

424
00:26:26,390 --> 00:26:30,960
<i>Your bright and innocent smile</i>

425
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:37,430
<i>Has made a fool out of me</i>

426
00:26:48,610 --> 00:26:49,680
<i>The one who left...</i>

427
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:52,120
- Jun Ho.
- Jun Ho.

428
00:26:52,780 --> 00:26:55,590
Don't make a scene and come with me.
Otherwise, I might just kill Baek Ho.

429
00:26:55,650 --> 00:26:57,250
What are you doing? Are you crazy?

430
00:26:57,550 --> 00:26:58,560
Come with me.

431
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:00,190
What's wrong with you?

432
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:01,890
What do you think you're doing?
Are you out of your mind?

433
00:27:02,390 --> 00:27:03,760
What about you?

434
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:05,330
This is the woman I was supposed to marry.

435
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:08,370
A brother wouldn't do this to the woman
who was to be his sister-in-law.

436
00:27:08,430 --> 00:27:11,200
- Get out of my way.
- It's over with you. This is insane!

437
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:12,500
Get out of my face!

438
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:14,940
Baek Ho!

439
00:27:18,410 --> 00:27:19,410
Baek Ho!

440
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,140
Are you out of your mind?

441
00:27:23,050 --> 00:27:26,550
Baek Ho! Let go of me!

442
00:27:27,180 --> 00:27:29,420
Jun Ho, let me go!

443
00:27:30,290 --> 00:27:32,060
If you leave, I'll lose my mind.

444
00:27:32,060 --> 00:27:33,320
- Baek Ho!
- Get in.

445
00:27:33,660 --> 00:27:34,860
- Get in.
- Baek Ho!

446
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:50,570
Jang Mi...

447
00:27:51,910 --> 00:27:52,910
Jang Mi!

448
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:54,880
Kang Jun Ho!

449
00:27:55,510 --> 00:27:57,010
- Kang Jun Ho!
- Baek Ho!

450
00:27:57,410 --> 00:27:59,450
- Jang Mi! Kang Jun Ho!
- Baek Ho

451
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:01,850
- Jang Mi! Kang Jun Ho!
- Let me out.

452
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,250
- Kang Jun Ho!
- I said, let me out!

453
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:06,190
- Kang Jun Ho!
- Open the door! I said, open it!

454
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:08,790
Kang Jun Ho!

455
00:28:09,130 --> 00:28:10,660
Jang Mi! Kang Jun Ho!

456
00:28:10,990 --> 00:28:12,060
Kang Jun Ho!

457
00:28:14,630 --> 00:28:15,700
Darn it!

458
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:50,870
(The First Man)

459
00:28:50,970 --> 00:28:53,070
Kang Jun Ho took our Jang Mi?

460
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:55,270
Why is he being so reckless?

461
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:56,910
Haven't you thought that
the more you act like this,

462
00:28:56,910 --> 00:28:58,740
the more you just push me away?

463
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:01,140
You found Kang Jun Ho's car
under an underpass?

464
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:02,410
Where is it?

465
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,480
Get lost while I'm asking nicely.

466
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:06,850
I'm the chairman's sister-in-law.

467
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:09,550
I heard
my late sister's daughter is alive,

468
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:10,790
and that's why I'm here.

469
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:12,990
The chairman's daughter is alive?

470
00:29:16,030 --> 00:29:18,030
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
